    <!-- Key Patterns -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-header"><h5 class="card-title mb-0"><i class="bi bi-gear me-2"></i>Database Patterns & Conventions</h5></div>
        <div class="card-body small">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Column Naming</strong>: SQL uses <code>[ST-CD]</code>, <code>[MAJ-CAT]</code>, <code>[BIN CAP]</code> (hyphens/spaces). EF models use <code>[Column("ST-CD")]</code> attribute mapping.</li>
                        <li><strong>NOLOCK</strong>: All read queries use <code>WITH (NOLOCK)</code> hint</li>
                        <li><strong>UNPIVOT</strong>: Sale/Display tables have 48 weekly columns. SPs UNPIVOT them to rows for processing. After UNPIVOT, original alias is invalid — use UNPIVOT alias.</li>
                        <li><strong>Week Columns</strong>: <code>WK-1</code> to <code>WK-48</code> represent fiscal weeks, not calendar weeks</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Nullable Types</strong>: Most decimal columns are <code>decimal?</code> in EF models. Always use <code>?? 0</code> when summing.</li>
                        <li><strong>Raw SQL</strong>: Dashboard KPIs + performance-critical queries use raw <code>SqlConnection</code>. CRUD uses EF Core.</li>
                        <li><strong>Dynamic SQL</strong>: Sub-level SPs use <code>sp_executesql</code> for dynamic table names. Temp tables must be CREATE'd in parent scope, INSERT from dynamic SQL.</li>
                        <li><strong>SqlBulkCopy</strong>: Bulk Upload uses SqlBulkCopy for 20L+ row performance</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
